## 3. LLM Tier Architecture

Three inference tiers, each with distinct latency, compute, and authority envelopes.

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TIER 1 — EDGE FAST                                                        │
│  Hardware:    Hailo-10H NPU                                                │
│  Model:       Phi-3-mini (3.8B), Moondream-2 (1.8B), Qwen2.5-0.5B        │
│  Latency:     < 200ms                                                      │
│  Authority:   PROPOSE only. Cannot directly write cmd.* paths.            │
│  Escalates:   When H_sem > 0.35 (see §5)                                  │
│  Context:     ≤ 1,024 tokens (hard cap enforced at world model build)     │
│  Use cases:   Routine navigation, sensor anomaly detection, UI parsing    │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TIER 2 — MEDIUM VERIFICATION                                              │
│  Hardware:    RPi 5 CPU (llama.cpp)                                        │
│  Model:       Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct (INT4 GGUF)                             │
│  Latency:     < 2s                                                         │
│  Authority:   AGREE / REFUSE on Tier 1 proposals. PROPOSE with CRITIQUE.  │
│  Escalates:   When H_sem > 0.45 or confidence < 0.70                      │
│  Context:     ≤ 4,096 tokens                                               │
│  Use cases:   Proposal critique, collision analysis, complex routing       │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TIER 3 — SOVEREIGN / CLOUD                                                │
│  Hardware:    Remote (Anthropic API) or local large GPU (future)           │
│  Model:       Claude Sonnet 4+ or equivalent                               │
│  Latency:     < 10s (cloud) or < 30s (local large)                        │
│  Authority:   Full DELEGATE authority. Can override Tier 1 and 2.         │
│  Escalates:   Never (terminal tier — escalation loops are a defect)       │
│  Context:     ≤ 32,768 tokens                                              │
│  Use cases:   Emergency resolution, voyage planning, policy decisions     │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 3.1 Tier Escalation Rules

1. Tier 1 **always** operates first on new data.
2. Tier 1 escalates to Tier 2 via UNCERTAINTY when entropy exceeds threshold.
3. Tier 2 escalates to Tier 3 only for: safety-critical events, multi-day planning, or
   when behavioral_trust of all available Tier 2 agents is below 0.60.
4. Escalation loops (Tier 3 → Tier 2 → Tier 3) are a protocol defect and must be detected
   and broken by the sovereign.
5. **Cloud access is optional.** All tiers operate in offline mode. Tier 3 degrades to
   "best available local model" when cloud is unreachable.

