## 5. Entropy-Based Sanity Checking

Edge models must continuously evaluate the quality of their own generation before
publishing output as a PROPOSE. This is done via logit-space entropy analysis.

### 5.1 Semantic Entropy

```
H_sem = -∑ p_i × log(p_i)   over the top-K candidate tokens at each decision step

where p_i = softmax(logit_i) of the top-K tokens
```

A low H_sem means the model is confident about what comes next.
A high H_sem means the model is uncertain — multiple tokens are nearly equally likely.

### 5.2 Entropy Decision Tree

```
                ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
                │  Generate action/trajectory tokens   │
                │  (Tier 1, Hailo-10H)                 │
                └──────────────────┬───────────────────┘
                                   │ Extract token logits
                                   ▼
                ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
                │  Compute H_sem across output tokens  │
                └──────────────────┬───────────────────┘
                                   │
        ┌──────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────┐
        ▼  H_sem ≤ 0.20                                       ▼  H_sem > 0.35
  ┌─────────────────┐                                   ┌──────────────────┐
  │  HIGH CERTAINTY │                                   │  UNCERTAIN       │
  │  Publish PROPOSE│                                   │  Publish         │
  │  with confidence│                                   │  UNCERTAINTY     │
  └─────────────────┘                                   │  escalate Tier 2 │
                                                         └──────────────────┘
        ▼  0.20 < H_sem ≤ 0.35
  ┌─────────────────────────┐
  │  MODERATE CERTAINTY     │
  │  Publish PROPOSE with   │
  │  reduced confidence,    │
  │  cross-validation check │
  └─────────────────────────┘
```

### 5.3 Entropy Thresholds by Tier

| Tier | Escalate threshold | Action |
|---|---|---|
| Tier 1 | H_sem > 0.35 | Publish UNCERTAINTY, hand to Tier 2 |
| Tier 2 | H_sem > 0.45 | Publish UNCERTAINTY, hand to Tier 3 |
| Tier 3 | H_sem > 0.60 | Publish ALERT, request human decision |

### 5.4 Context Fill Level Check

Additionally to entropy, check context fill before every generation:

```python
def pre_generation_check(context_tokens: int, budget: int) -> bool:
    fill_ratio = context_tokens / budget
    if fill_ratio > 0.60:
        # Reasoning degrades above 60% fill — escalate rather than proceed
        publish_uncertainty(reason="context_fill_above_threshold",
                            fill_ratio=fill_ratio)
        return False
    return True
```

