## 6. UNCERTAINTY Escalation Cascade

### 6.1 Cascade Flow

```
Tier 1 publishes UNCERTAINTY
    │
    ▼
Tier 2 receives UNCERTAINTY
    │  Fetches context_reference from ΣMatrix
    │  Runs deeper inference on the same context
    │
    ├─► If resolved: Tier 2 publishes PROPOSE (on behalf of original context)
    │
    └─► If not resolved: Tier 2 publishes UNCERTAINTY with tier=2
        │
        ▼
    Tier 3 (Sovereign) receives UNCERTAINTY
        │  Pulls full context from ΣMatrix
        │  Runs heavy inference
        │
        ├─► If resolved: Sovereign publishes PROPOSE + DELEGATE to execute
        │
        └─► If not resolved: Sovereign publishes ALERT
                              Requests human decision (VHF, visual, UI)
                              Executes fallback from original PROPOSE
```

### 6.2 Cascade Timeout

Each tier has a maximum response time after receiving UNCERTAINTY:

| Tier | Maximum response time |
|---|---|
| Tier 2 responds to Tier 1 | ≤ 5 seconds |
| Tier 3 responds to Tier 2 | ≤ 15 seconds |
| Human responds to ALERT | No timeout — execute fallback if human doesn't respond in scenario TTL |

If a tier does not respond within its timeout, the UNCERTAINTY is escalated
immediately to the next tier. The original PROPOSE's fallback remains armed.

