## 10. World Model Construction

### 10.1 World Model Snapshot

The world model is a point-in-time snapshot of all streams accessible to an agent,
enriched with effective_trust and age metadata.

```python
@dataclass
class WorldModelEntry:
    path:             str
    value:            Any
    effective_trust:  float     # computed at snapshot time
    age_ms:           float
    health:           str       # nominal | degraded | absent
    data_class:       str       # sensor | derived | inferred | command
    priority:         int
```

### 10.2 Stale Stream Handling

Streams marked `degraded` are included in the world model with a warning annotation.
Streams marked `absent` are **not** included — they are listed separately as
`missing_streams`.

```python
world_model = {
    "streams":         {path: WorldModelEntry, ...},  # nominal + degraded
    "missing_streams": [path, ...],                    # absent
    "snapshot_us":     timestamp,
    "total_streams":   42,
    "degraded_count":  3,
    "absent_count":    1
}
```

The agent prompt must include `missing_streams` so the LLM knows what it cannot see.
A world model with missing critical streams must trigger UNCERTAINTY.

